  "rationale": "The retrospective June 2025 official MTA evaluation supplies exact realized pilot and fare-resumption dates, the selected route set, and the fare-policy treatments. Four GTFS-addressable participants are currently trapped in the source-facing aggregate identities Bx18A/B and S46/S96. This recovery creates only the four atomic route identities, preserves both aggregate records for aggregate metrics, adds delivered project-to-route scope for all seven GTFS IDs, and represents fare resumption as a positive treatment distinct from the zero-fare treatment that ended. The seven-ID study projection is an addressability split of the report's five borough-level route selections; no aggregate metric is copied to an atomic route.",
